column3: >decided to dig up samples from this folder. I ended up zapping my drive in the process. BUT I had backups.

>The KawaiR50 was used for this beat. This has a very mechanical sound that I struggled with at first. It wasn't until I started making things faster an added velocity and ghost notes that things felt a little bit better. Also added some random pitch shifting too cuz why not it's there.
>thinking about using the LinnLinn-9000 drum samples today.

>using this in days 2 and 3 of novembeat, I found that this ride had a really weird ringing to it. It was a bit annoying. I ended up putting this really low in the mix. Layered with other things it wasn't too bad.
>a very gentle, subdued kick. pretty much melts and disappeared into the mix. it has a very different energy from the more forceful hard kicks I am used to working with. nice change of pace.
>this is presumably sampled from a real 808, so this rim definitely carries some nostalgic or 'classical' weight. definitely artificial, but not in your face about it.

>this is an 808 shaker that was part of the kit used in loop4. don't have much to say on this precise shaker because I haven't used these much. but it it was a really helpful layer to add to the mix to reinforce the 7/8 meters.

>not much to say on this snare really. 808, part of the kit I was using in novembeat 4. there were quite a few to choose from, but this one was gentler, with not too much body, and a little bit of low thud. I really wanted the entire kit to feel small and off to the side.
>a very vintage sounding electric mid tom. It's almost begging for sibling toms to play along.
>I did not actually end up using this.
>I think they are calling this a "wet" bass drum. I can almost hear why. There does seem to be a little bit of room here.
>This is a gated snare sound. Very 80s. There's a big space behind that snare, being snuffed out.
>as the filename suggests, a gated rimshot, a distinct 80s flavor.
